## What Was Built

### 1. RBAC Middleware ([rbac.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/middleware/rbac.ts))

- **Role hierarchy**: `USER < MODERATOR < ADMIN < SUPER_ADMIN`
- **Permission matrix**: 16 permissions mapped to roles
- **Middleware factories**: [requireRole()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/middleware/rbac.ts#115-135), [requirePermission()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/middleware/rbac.ts#138-157)
- **Anti-privilege-escalation**: [requireHigherRole()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/middleware/rbac.ts#178-193) guard
- **Migration path**: Designed to evolve from role-based → permission-based

### 2. Post State Machine ([post.state-machine.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.state-machine.ts))

- **Strict transition validation** for all 12 state transitions
- **Role-based authorization** per transition (who can perform each action)
- **Ownership checks** (e.g., only owner can submit/archive)
- **Helper utilities**: [getAvailableActions()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.state-machine.ts#133-157), [isPubliclyVisible()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.state-machine.ts#160-163), [isEditable()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.state-machine.ts#166-169)

### 3. Redis Distributed Locking ([moderation.lock.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/moderation/moderation.lock.ts))

- **Atomic lock acquisition**: `SET NX EX` pattern
- **5-minute TTL auto-release** (no deadlocks)
- **Lua script check-and-delete** (safe release)
- **Admin force-release** (override capability)
- **Lock info and scanning** (dashboard monitoring)
- **Lock extension** (during active review)

### 4. Priority Queue ([moderation.queue.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/moderation/moderation.queue.ts))

- **Redis Sorted Set**: O(log N) operations
- **Composite priority**: `risk_score * 0.4 + report_count * 0.3 + recency * 0.2 + trust * 0.1`
- **Queue depth monitoring** by priority tier (critical/high/medium/low)
- **Average wait time** metric for SLA tracking
- **7-day metadata TTL** for queue items

### 5. Kafka Event System ([moderation.events.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/moderation/moderation.events.ts))

- **12 event topics**: post.created, post.submitted_for_review, post.approved, etc.
- **Structured payloads** with correlation IDs and event versioning
- **Graceful error handling** (best-effort, never blocks main flow)
- **Key-based partitioning** (postId/userId for ordering guarantees)

### 6. Audit Service ([audit.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/audit/audit.service.ts) + [audit.repository.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/audit/audit.repository.ts))

- **Fire-and-forget logging** (never blocks main request)
- **Paginated queries** with 9 filter dimensions
- **Resource history** tracking (full timeline per entity)
- **Admin activity metrics** (who did what, how much)
- **Action distribution** (for spike detection/alerting)

### 7. Database Schema ([schema.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/db/schema.ts))

- **Posts table**: Added `risk_score`, `reviewed_by`, `reviewed_at`, `escalatedTo`, `escalationReason`
- **New `moderation_logs` table**: Every moderation action with full context
- **Optimized indexes**:
  - `pending_review_risk_idx` — queue performance (status + risk_score DESC + created_at ASC)
  - `published_feed_idx` — feed query performance (status + published_at DESC)  
  - `reviewer_idx` — moderator activity tracking
  - `mod_log_*` — moderation log indexes (post, moderator, action)
- **Updated status enum**: Added `APPROVED`, `REMOVED` states; removed `AUTO_APPROVED`

### 8. Post Service Rewrite ([post.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.service.ts))

- **Pre-moderation enforcement**: Posts default to `PENDING_REVIEW` (never auto-publish)
- **State machine integration**: All transitions validated
- **New methods**: [submitForReview()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.service.ts#72-109), [resubmitPost()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.service.ts#176-218), [getUserPosts()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.service.ts#219-228), [onPostPublished()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.service.ts#277-304)
- **Deferred processing**: Hashtags/mentions only processed after approval
- **Edit restrictions**: Only DRAFT/NEEDS_REVISION/REJECTED posts editable

### 9. Post Repository Updates ([post.repository.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.repository.ts))

- **Removed AUTO_APPROVED bypass**: No more random AI score simulation
- **Added [updateStatus()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/post/post.repository.ts#229-245)**: For state machine transitions
- **Visibility enforcement**: Only `PUBLISHED` in public view (no `AUTO_APPROVED`)

### 10. Moderation Service Rewrite ([moderation.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/moderation/moderation.service.ts))

- **Full orchestration**: State machine → Lock → DB transition → Queue → Events → Audit
- **Atomic moderation flow**:
  1. Validate transition (state machine)
  2. Acquire Redis lock
  3. Update database (transaction)
  4. Dequeue from Redis
  5. Emit Kafka events
  6. Write audit log
  7. Release lock (always, even on error)

### 11. Admin Service Enhancement ([admin.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/admin/admin.service.ts))

- **User management**: [suspendUser()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/admin/admin.service.ts#78-119), [unsuspendUser()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/admin/admin.service.ts#120-150), [assignRole()](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/modules/admin/admin.service.ts#151-209)
- **Anti-privilege-escalation**: Cannot suspend ADMIN, cannot self-assign roles
- **Role assignment rules**: Only SUPER_ADMIN can promote to ADMIN
- **Kafka events**: UserSuspended, UserRoleChanged for downstream services

### 12. tRPC Layer ([trpc.ts](file:///c:/Users/suraj/Desktop/socialmedia/backend/src/trpc/trpc.ts))

- **New `moderatorProcedure`**: MODERATOR + ADMIN access
- **Three-tier access**: `protectedProcedure` < `moderatorProcedure` < `adminProcedure`
- **Updated routers**: Moderation, admin, and post routers with proper access controls

